{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make impersonating military personnel a specific criminal offence",
        "additional_details": "\u2018Stolen Valour\u2019 is the term commonly applied to individuals wearing military medals or decorations that they have not been awarded, with the intent to deceive or defraud.\r\n \r\nThis behaviour has a damaging effect on true veterans who 1) may find themselves under unfair/intense scrutiny and 2) cause a backlash against our heroic military personnel veterans & serving members alike.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to put in place legislation to create a new specific offence of impersonating military personnel in order to deceive and/or defraud for personal gain.",
